Top Fix Says Its Operating Profit Declined by 16% During the Second Half

-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 
2011-02-14T14:17:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/top-fix-says-its-operating-profit-declined-by-16-during-the-second-half.html
Top Fix Ltd., a South African
provider of scaffolding to the construction and chemical
industries, said operating profit for the six months to December
fell 16 percent to 17.3 million rand from a year earlier.  The company commented in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Renee Bonorchis in Johannesburg at 
 rbonorchis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  